What you need to know:

Though this is not the first time for the Nile to burst its banks, victims say this is the worst case of flooding they have ever witnessed.Ethiopia has long been arguing that the Grand Ethiopia’s Renaissance Dam (GERD), being built near the Sudanese border, will ease the severity of flooding in Sudan.Sudan and Egypt fear that Ethiopia’s $4.8 billion mega dam project will eventually diminish their historic water share from the Nile River.